      "Every June, when the lavender began to bloom along the lower field, Ines helped her mother lift the heavy hive frames, checking each one for the telltale glisten of new honey.",
      "Her mother moved among the bees without gloves, humming under her breath, and claimed the bees could sense a nervous hand from a steady one. Ines was not sure she believed this, but she had never been stung while humming too.",
      "This year, though, one hive had fallen silent. No bees streamed from its entrance, and the frames inside were empty of the restless, golden motion Ines had grown up with.",
